Notes on ImageAnalysis:

  The image content is written per slice and is organised by plane:

    U
    V
    W

  detector_image_*_index and detector_image_*_adc form sparse detector-image
  content for each plane.

  semantic_image_*_label stores per-pixel semantic labels, and
  slice_semantic_active_pixels_* stores counts per semantic label for the
  corresponding plane.

  semantic_label_names is populated from
  image::SemanticClassifier::semantic_label_names and provides the label-name
  ordering for the semantic-count vectors.

  The inference branches are optional and depend on whether the production job
  provides InferencePredProduct and InferencePerfProduct using the configured
  tags.

