Notes on TruthAnalysis:

  TruthAnalysis is only meaningful for non-data samples. On data events the
  truth-oriented branches are reset to empty or sentinel values.

  The truth-neutrino fields are taken from the first MCTruth neutrino record
  in the event when NeutrinoSet() is true.

  prim_* vectors are aligned element-by-element and describe primary final
  state MC particles with Process() == "primary" and StatusCode() == 1.

  prim_dau_* uses a nested-per-primary layout for PDG, energy, momentum, and
  vertex content. prim_dau_process_flat and prim_dau_process_idx provide a
  flattened process-string representation parallel to those per-primary
  daughter collections.

  prim_bt_completeness and prim_bt_purity are populated during analyseSlice()
  by matching the selected reconstructed slice hits back to the truth primary
  particles.

