Notes on LambdaAnalysis_tool:

  LambdaAnalysis_tool is only meaningful for non-data samples. On data events
  its branches are reset to empty or sentinel values.

  truth_* branches summarize generator-level strange final states from the
  MCTruth record.

  truth_has_nc_strangeness is true when the event is neutral current and has
  at least one strange hadron in the generator final state.

  truth_has_g4_lambda0_to_ppi and truth_n_g4_lambda0_to_ppi summarize Geant4
  Lambda candidates with matched proton-plus-pion daughters.

  The g4_lambda_* vectors are aligned element-by-element, one entry per
  matched Geant4 Lambda decay candidate.

  The g4_lambda_pr_* and g4_lambda_*_true_hits branches are filled during
  analyseSlice() by matching the selected reconstructed slice content against
  the truth muon, proton, and pion track IDs.

