Notes
-----

The full event tree schema is not fixed solely by EventSelectionFilter.

Additional branches can be added by:

  SelectionToolBase::setBranches(...)
  AnalysisToolBase::setBranches(...)

So the persistent schema of a produced event tree depends on the configured
selection tool and analysis tools used in production.

In particular, EventWeightAnalysis adds a substantial set of optional weight
branches that are important for systematic reweighting studies.

ImageAnalysis can also add large sparse-image, semantic-label, and inference
payload branches that are relevant for ML-oriented downstream workflows and
training snapshots.

TruthAnalysis can add a large truth-level description of the interaction,
beamline parentage, and truth-primary topology for MC samples.

LambdaAnalysis_tool can add a more specialized strange-particle truth summary,
including generator strange content and Geant4 Lambda-to-proton-pion decay
topology.

SubRun
------

The SubRun tree contains per-subrun normalization and exposure information:

  run                int
  subRun             int
  pot                double
  n_beam_gates       long long
  n_ext_gates        long long
  pot_per_gate       double
  ext_equiv_pot      double

How this relates to this repository
-----------------------------------

SampleIO:
  Uses the upstream SubRun tree information to derive run and subrun
  provenance and exposure summaries for persistent sample objects.

DatasetIO:
  Collects multiple persistent SampleIO objects into one keyed dataset
  container and stores the per-sample normalization values.

EventListIO:
  Reads the job ROOT files referenced by DatasetIO, applies a TTreeFormula
  selection to the upstream event tree, and copies the selected event entries
  plus the upstream SubRun tree into one persistent event-list file.
